parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seat belt can cause the seat belt to become inoperable, leading to a lack of restraint in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract
the seat belt does not engage when the door is closed
the seat belt sticks in the open or closed position
the seat belt buckle releases from the seat belt webbing
the seat belt warning light keeps ringing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause extended stopping distances, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floorboard
and the stopping distance is extended.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause brake fluid leakage, brake inoperability, and accidents.
symptoms: Crack in the ABS control unit cylinder

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake rotors can cause the vehicle to pull to one side, vibrations, and overheating, leading to accidents and loss of control.
The failure of the brake shoes or discs can cause noisy brakes, vibrations, and loss of braking power, leading to accidents.
The failure of the proportional valve can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to accidents and loss of control.

Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause sudden and unexpected downshifting, which can lead to loss of control.
Transmission fluid leaks can cause the transmission to fail prematurely, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: need to purchase a new transmission.
